  "text": "GASZ is a 475 amino acid Germ cell-specific protein with four Ankyrin repeats, a Sterile alpha motif, and a basic leucine Zipper domain [CITATION_1] that is conserved across vertebrate evolution in amphibians, fish, birds, and mammals [CITATION_2] . Our previous studies have shown that GASZ localizes to the Balbiani body, a nuage structure in Xenopus laevis oocytes. The high degree of evolutionary conservation of GASZ in vertebrates and the potential localization of GASZ to a conserved germline-specific structure stimulated our interest to determine the expression and essential roles of GASZ in nuage and its germline function in mammals.",
